check_library(25.10)                                      check_library(25.10)

Name
       check_library  - Checks the problematic cells that cause issues such as
       bad geometries for DRC and bad pin access for routing

Syntax
       check_library

       [-help]

       [-place  [-cell  <cell_name>|-all_lib_cell][-legal_frequency  ]  [-file
       <fileName>] ]

       Checks  the  problematic cells that cause issues such as bad geometries
       for DRC and bad pin access for routing. You can specify a library  cell
       or  a partition cell. It also performs checks for the multi-height cell
       legal frequency. The report is dumped into an output file.

Parameters
       -all_lib_cell
              Specifies to check all library cells.

       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the cell to check.

       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the output file.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each check_library parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man check_library.

       -legal_frequency
              Specifies to check multi-height cell legal frequency

       -place Specifies to do library checking for placement.

Example
              * The following command checks the buf01 cell:

       check_library -place -cell buf01

       Estimated cell power/ground rail width = 0.021 um

       *info: running library checker ...

       *info: total 1 cell checked.

       *reporting cell (buf01) ...

       reporting cell drc : "legal"

       reporting cell pin access : "legal"

       reporting cell symmetry : cell (buf01) has lef symmetry X Y

       reporting cell pin alignment : "legal"

       reporting cell legal frequency ...

        cell  (buf01)  legalization frequency: one legal location out of every
       1.25 sites

